<paragraph blockId="6.[136,1452,1454,1553]" pageId="6" pageNumber="215">
Endemic to 
<collectingRegion box="[271,382,1454,1480]" country="Australia" name="Tasmania" pageId="6" pageNumber="215">Tasmania</collectingRegion>
. This lichenicolous species is most similar to the Australian species, 
<taxonomicName box="[1154,1259,1455,1480]" class="Lecanoromycetes" family="Xylographaceae" genus="Lambiella" kingdom="Fungi" pageId="6" pageNumber="215" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="exigua">
<emphasis box="[1154,1259,1455,1480]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="215">L. exigua</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
* 
<superScript attach="none" box="[1273,1289,1454,1468]" fontSize="6" pageId="6" pageNumber="215">1*</superScript>
, which differs by its non-lichenicolous habit and the absence of 
<emphasis box="[679,775,1490,1516]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="215">sedifolia</emphasis>
-grey pigment in the epihymenium. The relationship between these two species deserves further study.
</paragraph>
